I always use Ryder, much better trucks and aluminum trailers, much lighter,
better maintained equipment and if they don't have the truck requested when
you arrive they move you up to the next size at no extra charge. In my
opinion U-Haul sucks. When I rented the Ryder back east to haul the BD's
back I bought, the only rental trucks I was passing and seeing broken down
where U-Hauls.

